state)\n- Calls `streamLiveLogs()` (lines 640-673)\n- Subscribes to `logBroadcast.Subscribe(runID)`\n- Streams each log line as it arrives with type: \"log\"\n- Closes stream when broadcaster finishes (run completes)\n\n**Scenario C: Completed Run** (no filters)\n- First checks for `full.log` file\n- If exists: sends it as type \"full_log\" (entire unified log)\n- Otherwise: reconstructs from captures\n  - For each capture, sends \"step_started\" entry\n  - For step_completed entries, reads per-step output file and sends as \"step_completed\" with output\n\n**Key Implementation Detail** (line 532-533):\n```\n// Do NOT fall back to container.log — it contains unfiltered output\n// from ALL steps and would show wrong content for this step.\n```\n\n### 5. **Web UI Log Streaming**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 818-945)\n\n`handleAPIStream()` serves Server-Sent Events (SSE) for real-time log display:\n\n**For Completed Runs**:\n- Reads `full.log` from disk (lines 891-912)\n- Parses \"[timestamp] [type] content\" format using regex\n- Parses LLM lines from Claude stream-json to human text\n- Sends as SSE with JSON payload\n\n**For Active Runs**:\n- Subscribes to `logBroadcast` (line 860)\n- Streams each LogLine as JSON SSE data event\n- Closes on broadcaster finish\n\n**Log Parsing** (`parseLLMLogLine`, lines 914-928):\n- Calls `logstream.ParseClaudeLine()` on \"llm\" type lines\n- Extracts human-readable text from Claude stream-json\n- Skips protocol-only events (system/user/etc.)\n\n### 6. **Claude Stream JSON Parsing**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go`\n\n**`ParseClaudeLine()` (lines 13-46)**:\n- Parses single stream-json line\n- Extracts text from \"assistant\" events (lines 93-125)\n- Extracts from \"result\" events (lines 222-232)\n- Handles \"content_block_delta\" (streaming format, lines 127-141)\n- Handles \"content_block_start\" for tool invocations (lines 143-159)\n- Returns `(text, ok bool)` - `ok=false` means skip (protocol-only)\n\n**`ParseClaudeStream()` (lines 54-91)**:\n- Batch parser for full output\n- Detects if input is stream-json by checking for JSON lines\n- Falls back to plaintext if no JSON detected\n- Preserves non-JSON lines (like shell output)\n\n### 7. **CLI Log Command**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/cmd/cloche/main.go` (lines 263-347)\n\n`cloche logs <run-id> [--step <name>] [--type <full|script|llm>] [--follow]`\n\n- Parses filter flags\n- **Without `--follow`**:\n  - Calls gRPC `StreamLogs()` with filters\n  - Receives entries and prints based on type:\n    - \"step_started\" → `--- {stepName} started ---`\n    - \"step_completed\" → `--- {stepName}: {result} ---` with message output\n    - \"full_log\" → Raw full.log content\n    - Other types → Parsed via `logstream.ParseClaudeStream()`\n\n- **With `--follow`**:\n  - Connects to HTTP SSE endpoint `/api/runs/{id}/stream`\n  - Color-codes by type: blue for status, green for llm\n  - Stops on \"event: done\"\n\n### 8. **Log Output Directory Structure**\n\n```\n.cloche/{runID}/output/\n├── full.log              # Unified timestamped log ([timestamp] [type] content)\n├── {stepName}.log        # Per-step script output\n├── llm-{stepName}.log    # Per-step LLM output (Claude stream-json)\n└── container.log         # Raw Docker container logs (internal, not indexed)\n```\n\n### 9. **SQLite Implementation**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` (lines 273-362)\n\n**`step_executions` table**:\n- Columns: `run_id`, `step_name`, `result`, `started_at`, `completed_at`, `logs`, `git_ref`\n- Records inserted for step start (result=NULL) and completion (result set)\n\n**`log_files` table**:\n- Columns: `run_id`, `step_name`, `file_type`, `file_path`, `file_size`, `created_at`\n- Indexes log files extracted after run completion\n\n### 10. **Log Broadcasting (Live Streaming)**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`\n\n**`LogLine` struct** (lines 8-13):\n- Fields: `Timestamp`, `Type` (status/script/llm), `Content`, `StepName`\n\n**`Broadcaster` thread-safe pub/sub**:\n- `Subscribe(runID)` - Returns Subscriber with buffered channel (256 buffer)\n- `Publish(runID, line)` - Sends to all subscribers (non-blocking, drops on full)\n- `Finish(runID)` - Closes all subscriber channels\n- `IsActive(runID)` - Check if broadcast still running\n\n### 11. **Step Filtering Logic**\n\nFrom protocol `/workspace/internal/protocol/status.go`:\n- Message types: `MsgStepStarted`, `MsgStepCompleted`, `MsgRunCompleted`, `MsgLog`, etc.\n- Each message includes optional `StepName` field\n\nFiltering is applied at:\n1. **Storage**: Captures indexed by step name\n2. **Retrieval**: `LogStore.GetLogFilesByStep()` filters at query level\n3. **File Paths**: Convention-based lookups by step name\n4. **API Response**: Filters applied to SSE stream output\n\n### 12. **History Log**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/protocol/history.go`\n\nLocal history tracking (not for streaming):\n- Writes to `.cloche/history.log` (not persisted to daemon)\n- Records step completion with timestamp, result, and optional output\n- For script steps: includes indented output lines\n- For agent steps: notes \"(agent)\" marker\n\n---\n\nThis architecture provides:\n- **Live streaming** for active runs via broadcaster\n- **Historical replay** for completed runs from indexed log files\n- **Step-level filtering** via LogStore queries and file path conventions\n- **Stream parsing** from Claude's stream-json format to human text\n- **Web UI SSE support** with full.log serving and live broadcast subscription\n- **CLI integration** with optional `--step` and `--type` filters"}],"totalDurationMs":113739,"totalTokens":80693,"totalToolUseCount":37,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1170,"cache_read_input_tokens":76784,"output_tokens":2734,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1170},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
