{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QDucciiBqDxyTUdbSwXj1F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the complete picture. Let me identify the issues:\n\n1. **Web UI - Step Output for Active Runs**: When a step is expanded in the web UI during an active run, it calls `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output` which is `handleAPIStepOutput`. This handler only looks at log files on disk (from completed runs). For active runs, log files don't exist yet on disk because they're only extracted from the container after the run completes. So the handler returns \"step output not found\" (404).\n\n2. **Web UI - Step Output for Active Runs**: The web UI needs to show historical + live logs for a specific step. \n\nThe core issue is that there's no way to retrieve accumulated logs for a step from the broadcaster or stream live updates for a specific step in real-time.\n\n3. **CLI - `cloche logs --step <name>` for Active Runs**: In `StreamLogs`, when `req.StepName != \"\"`, it goes to `streamFilteredLogs()` which only looks at log files on disk. For active runs, these files don't exist yet. It should first check if the run is active and, if so, stream from the broadcaster filtered by step name.\n\n4. **Broadcaster - No History Buffer**: The broadcaster is purely live-streaming with no mechanism to retain historical logs, so once a line is published and consumed, it's gone.\n\nTo fix this, I need to add a per-run history buffer to the broadcaster so new subscribers get the full context before receiving live updates. Then I'll update `streamFilteredLogs` to check if a run is active and pull historical logs from the broadcaster filtered by step before streaming live updates. For the API step output handler, when the run is active and no disk files exist, I should fetch the historical logs from the broadcaster for that step. Finally, I'll extend the API stream handler to support step filtering in the same way.\n\nThe core issue is that the broadcaster doesn't persist any history—it only sends live updates to current subscribers. I need to add a history field to store all published lines per run, along with a method to retrieve them and another to filter by step name. This way, when someone expands a step during an active run, they can get the full context immediately.\n\nThen I'll update `handleAPIStepOutput` to check the broadcaster history when log files don't exist on disk yet, and modify `StreamLogs` to combine historical data with the live stream when filtering by step. The web UI can then fetch the step output as a live-updating stream that starts with all captured logs and continues with new ones. web UI needs an SSE endpoint for step-level streaming.\n\nLet me plan more carefully:\n\n**For the Web UI:**\n- The current behavior when expanding a step is a one-shot `fetch('/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output')` \n- For completed runs, this works fine (returns the log file content)\n- For active runs, we need to: (1) send historical logs, (2) then stream live updates\n- The simplest approach: add a step-specific SSE streaming endpoint `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/stream` that sends history then streams live, and update the web UI to use it for active runs\n\nActually wait - let me re-read the web UI code more carefully. When expanding a step during an active run, the fetch returns 404 (\"step output not found\"), and \"No output available.\" is shown. The fix should make this work.\n\nI'm weighing three options: serve accumulated broadcaster history through the existing endpoint to immediately fix the fetch call, add a dedicated SSE endpoint for proper streaming, or make the current endpoint handle both one-shot and streaming based on headers. I think the best path is adding broadcaster history first, then layering in a step-specific SSE stream endpoint while updating the web UI to use it. E for active runs\n- Update `streamFilteredLogs` in gRPC to serve from broadcaster history + live stream for active runs (fixes CLI)\n\nActually, let me simplify. The task says \"show all logs captured to date for that step, then continue updating with new streaming lines.\" The simplest implementation:\n\n1. Add history buffer to Broadcaster\n2. For CLI `cloche logs --step <name>`:\n   - If run is active: serve history filtered by step, then live stream filtered by step\n   - If run is complete: serve from log files (existing behavior)\n3. For Web UI step expansion:\n   - If run is active: serve history from broadcaster, and the 2s polling will keep refreshing\n   - Actually, the better UX is to SSE stream for the step\n\nLet me look at this pragmatically. The Web UI already polls steps every 2 seconds for active runs. The step output accordion refetches on each poll cycle if it's open, so if I just fix `handleAPIStepOutput` to return broadcaster history for active runs, the web UI will naturally update every 2 seconds. For true live streaming, I could add a step-specific stream endpoint and update the web UI to use it.\n\nBut let me keep it simpler first. I'll add history tracking to Broadcaster with methods to retrieve and subscribe to historical data, fix the step output handler to use that history for active runs, update the gRPC logs endpoint to pull from the broadcaster for active runs with step filtering, and then add a step-specific SSE endpoint for the Web UI to consume.\n\nModifying Broadcaster... When expanding a step for a completed run, I'll stick with the existing fetch behavior. Before diving into implementation, let me check what tests are already in place so I can follow the established patterns.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5707,"cache_read_input_tokens":50932,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":5707},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f92ec9ed-6750-474b-9b04-f794ca7ab54a","uuid":"bd01f20d-67c8-465a-aa7b-3871f5662bfd"}
