{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01HDMG1whHKf8LyjTgXTA6Gx","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of the changes:\n\n**Broadcaster** (`internal/logstream/broadcaster.go`):\n- Added `history []LogLine` to `runBroadcast` to accumulate all published lines per run\n- `Publish()` now creates run entries on first publish and records to history\n- Added `History(runID)` to retrieve accumulated log lines for a run\n- Added `SubscribeWithHistory(runID)` for gap-free subscribe-with-replay\n\n**gRPC Server** (`internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n- `StreamLogs` with step/type filter on active runs now routes to `streamFilteredLive()` instead of `streamFilteredLogs()`\n- New `streamFilteredLive()` method: sends broadcaster history filtered by step/type, then streams live updates with the same filter\n\n**Web Handler** (`internal/adapters/web/handler.go`):\n- `handleAPIStepOutput` now falls back to broadcaster history for active runs when no log files exist on disk\n- New `handleAPIStepStream` SSE endpoint (`GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/stream`) that serves step-specific history + live streaming\n\n**Web UI** (`internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`):\n- Step expansion for active runs uses `EventSource` (SSE) for live streaming instead of one-shot fetch\n- Step expansion for completed runs still uses one-shot fetch\n- Properly cleans up SSE connections when collapsing steps\n\n**Tests**: 8 new tests across broadcaster, gRPC server, and web handler covering history, subscribe-with-history, step filtering on active runs, and step SSE streaming.\n\nCLOCHE_RESULT:success"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":358,"cache_read_input_tokens":106067,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":358},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"pa